"title": "7512: Gentiles, in NT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7512",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Although Jesus Christ initially preached to Israel, his mission was soon extended to the Gentiles. From the outset, the Christian church accepted Gentiles as full members, refusing to make any distinction between Jew and Gentile. Paul, “the apostle to the Gentiles”, laid particular emphasis on their role in the purposes of God.</p>\n<h2>Gentiles in Jesus Christ's earthly ministry</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's contact with Gentiles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:5-Matt8:13\">MAT 8:5–8:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:1-Luke7:10\">LUK 7:1–7:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:21-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:21–15:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:24-Mark7:30\">MRK 7:24–7:30</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's teaching concerning Gentiles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:33-Matt21:43\">MAT 21:33–21:43</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:1-Mark12:11\">MRK 12:1–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:9-Luke20:16\">LUK 20:9–20:16</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:20-Luke21:24\">LUK 21:20–21:24</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's instructions to his disciples concerning Gentiles</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:5-Matt10:6\">MAT 10:5–10:6</a> <em>Initially the disciples were commanded to preach to Jews, but after his resurrection, Jesus Christ commissioned them to preach the message of the kingdom of God to all nations.</em><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a></strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:15-Mark16:16\">MRK 16:15–16:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:46-Luke24:47\">LUK 24:46–24:47</a></p>\n<h2>Peter sent to Gentiles</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:28\">ACT 10:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:9-Acts10:20\">ACT 10:9–10:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:5-Acts11:14\">ACT 11:5–11:14</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:44-Acts10:48\">ACT 10:44–10:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:15\">ACT 11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:7-Acts15:8\">ACT 15:7–15:8</a></p>\n<h2>Paul, apostle to the Gentiles</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:7-Gal2:9\">GAL 2:7–2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:15\">ACT 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:21\">ACT 22:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:15-Acts26:23\">ACT 26:15–26:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:13-Rom1:15\">ROM 1:13–1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:13\">ROM 11:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:15-Rom15:19\">ROM 15:15–15:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:2\">GAL 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:1\">EPH 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:7\">1TI 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:17\">2TI 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>Rejected by Jews, Paul turns more to the Gentiles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:6\">ACT 18:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:46\">ACT 13:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:28\">ACT 28:28</a></p>\n<h2>Response of the Gentiles to Paul's preaching</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:48\">ACT 13:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:1-Acts14:2\">ACT 14:1–14:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:12\">ACT 15:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:19\">ACT 21:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:23-1Cor1:24\">1CO 1:23–1:24</a></p>\n<h2>Difficulties concerning the acceptance of Gentiles into the church</h2>\n<h3>The question of mixing with Gentiles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:2-Acts11:3\">ACT 11:2–11:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:15-Acts11:18\">ACT 11:15–11:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:12-Gal2:13\">GAL 2:12–2:13</a></p>\n<h3>The question of circumcision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:5-Acts15:31\">ACT 15:5–15:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:1-Gal2:5\">GAL 2:1–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1-Gal5:6\">GAL 5:1–5:6</a></p>\n<h2>NT teaching on Gentiles</h2>\n<h3>Gentiles now share the inheritance of God's people Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:13\">EPH 2:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9-Rev5:10\">REV 5:9–5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:29\">ROM 3:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:11-Rom11:21\">ROM 11:11–11:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:9\">REV 7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:6\">REV 14:6</a></p>\n<h3>There is no distinction between Jews and Gentiles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:28\">GAL 3:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:9-Rom2:11\">ROM 2:9–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19-Eph2:20\">EPH 2:19–2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:11\">COL 3:11</a></p>\n<h2>God calls both Jew and Gentile</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:47-Acts13:48\">ACT 13:47–13:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:24-Rom9:26\">ROM 9:24–9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:24-1Cor1:25\">1CO 1:24–1:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:17\">2TI 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>Both Jews and Gentiles are justified by faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:6-Gal3:14\">GAL 3:6–3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:9-Rom4:12\">ROM 4:9–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:16\">ROM 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:6\">GAL 5:6</a></p>",
